            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@osgx: that wording (or something extremely similar) is found in the POSIX specification for &lt;a href=&quot;http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/utilities/c99.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;c99&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  which is the POSIX name for the C compiler.  (The POSIX 2008 standard could hardly refer to C11; the 2013 update to POSIX 2008 did not change the C standard that it referred to.)&lt;/span&gt;

